.TH SP-SIM-OBSERVER 1 "Spherepop Tools" "1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
sp-sim-observer \- emit disclosed, semantically empty signals to study misattribution
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sp-sim-observer
.RB [ \-n " lines" ]
.RB [ \-s " seed" ]
.RB [ \-o " out.log" ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
sp-sim-observer generates a log of authoritative-looking lines that are
explicitly disclosed as semantically empty. The purpose is to study observer
misattribution and attribution error.
.PP
This tool performs no diagnostics and accesses no external systems.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-n " lines"
Number of lines to emit (default: 40).
.TP
.BI \-s " seed"
Integer seed (default: 123).
.TP
.BI \-o " file"
Output log file (default: ./observer.log).
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success, non-zero on error.
.SH SEE ALSO
sp-audit-legibility(1)

